article.headline: Tennessee Tech 117, Bluefield 88
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Fisher scored 23 points and Tennessee Tech pulled away late in the first half for a 117-88 victory Tuesday over Bluefield. Daniel Northern added 19 points and Amadi McKenzie 16 for Tech (2-5). Bluefield (7-2) was led by Curtis Dixon with 21 points and Dontae Gholson with 16. Tennessee Tech led 31-30 until going on a 21-5 run over a five-minute span late in the first half to break the game open. Tech shot 58.4 percent to 41.3 percent for the Rams. Tech had a big advantage at the free throw line, making 19-of-33 to 6-of-12 by Bluefield. The 205 points were the second highest total in the 31-year history of the Eblen Center.
